ZH: 造纸术是中国古代的一项伟大发明。
EN: Papermaking is a great invention of ancient China.
ZH: 千年前的造纸术在世界上产生了深远的影响。
EN: Papermaking from a thousand years ago had a profound impact on the world.
ZH: 造纸术的出现大大促进了文字的传播。
EN: The invention of papermaking greatly facilitated the spread of written language.
ZH: 中国在古代就掌握了高度发达的造纸术。
EN: Ancient China had already mastered highly advanced papermaking techniques.
ZH: 造纸术的出现代表了人类文明的进步。
EN: The invention of papermaking represents the progress of human civilization.
ZH: 造纸术不仅仅是中国的独创，也启发了其他文化。
EN: Papermaking is not only an invention of China, it also inspired other cultures.
ZH: 造纸术的技艺需要经过长时间的磨练才能掌握。
EN: The skill of papermaking requires long-term practice to master.
ZH: 造纸术的本质是将纤维制成纸张。
EN: The essence of papermaking is turning fibers into paper.
ZH: 造纸术的发明给书写和印刷提供了基础材料。
EN: The invention of papermaking provided the foundation materials for writing and printing.
ZH: 不同的纤维在造纸术中有着各自的应用。
EN: Different fibers have their own applications in the process of papermaking.
ZH: 现代造纸术通过机械化大幅度提高了生产效率。
EN: Modern papermaking has greatly increased production efficiency through mechanization.
ZH: 造纸术让纸张成为了人们生活中不可或缺的物品。
EN: Papermaking has made paper an indispensable part of people's lives.
ZH: 造纸术不仅应用于书写和印刷，还应用于包装等领域。
EN: Papermaking is applied not only in writing and printing but also in packaging and other fields.
ZH: 我们现在可以自己动手用造纸术制作纸张。
EN: Nowadays, we can make paper using papermaking techniques by ourselves.
ZH: 传统的造纸术在一些偏远地区仍然保持着传承。
EN: Traditional papermaking techniques are still preserved in some remote areas.
ZH: 创新的造纸术正在不断地涌现和发展。
EN: Innovative papermaking techniques are constantly emerging and developing.
ZH: 在古代，学习造纸术被认为是一项高贵的技艺。
EN: In ancient times, learning papermaking was considered a noble skill.
ZH: 造纸术的技术要点需要经过严格的学习和实践。
EN: The technical points of papermaking require rigorous learning and practice.
ZH: 现代造纸术已经取得了很多技术突破和创新。
EN: Modern papermaking has achieved many technological breakthroughs and innovations.
